## ⚡ V. The Proverbs (The CLI Cheat Sheet)

Memorize these incantations, for they will save you in times of darkness.

### Building & Running
* **Build an Image:** `docker build -t my-app:v1 .`
* **Run interactively (for testing):** `docker run -it -p 8080:8080 my-app:v1`
* **Run in the background (detached):** `docker run -d -p 80:8080 --name my-running-app my-app:v1`

### Observation & Debugging
* **List running containers:** `docker ps`
* **List ALL containers (even dead ones):** `docker ps -a`
* **View the logs of a container:** `docker logs -f [CONTAINER_ID]`
* **Enter a running container (The ultimate debug):** `docker exec -it [CONTAINER_ID] /bin/sh` *(or `/bin/bash`)*

### Cleansing the System
* **Stop a container:** `docker stop [CONTAINER_ID]`
* **Delete a container:** `docker rm [CONTAINER_ID]`
* **Delete an Image:** `docker rmi [IMAGE_ID]`
* **The Holy Purge (Deletes all stopped containers, unused networks, and dangling images):** `docker system prune -a`

